think%20too%20hard%2C%20or%20that%20upsets%20them%20emotionally.%20If%20they%20have%20a%20goal%2C%20Jigsaw%20found%2C%20it's%20to%20learn%20what%20they%20need%20to%20know%20to%20remain%20cool%20and%20conversant%20in%20their%20chosen%20social%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20old%20guard%20is%20like%3A%20'Yeah%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20care%20ultimately%20about%20the%20truth%2C'%26quot%3B%20Green%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Gen%20Z%20take%20is%3A%20'You%20can%20tell%20me%20%3Cem%3Eyour%3C%2Fem%3E%20truth%20and%20what%20%3Cem%3Eyou%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethink%20is%20important.'%26quot%3B%20What%20establishes%20the%20relevance%20of%20a%20claim%20isn't%20some%20established%20notion%20of%20authority.%20It's%20the%20social%20signals%20they%20get%20from%20their%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EJigsaw's%20research%20doesn't%20purport%20to%20be%20statistically%20significant.%20They%20didn't%20poll%20a%20large%20group%20of%20Gen%20Z%20users%20about%20their%20digital%20habits.%20Instead%2C%20they%20relied%20on%20intense%20interviews%20with%20a%20handful%20of%2013-%20to%2024-year-olds%20from%20a%20representative%20range%20of%20demographics%2C%20classes%2C%20and%20genders.%20They%20were%20doing%20what%20anthropologists%20do%20in%20the%20field%20%E2%80%94%20looking%20for%20qualitative%20depth%20rather%20than%20quantitative%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20they%20heard%20surprised%20them.%20Young%20folks%20basically%20say%20they%20see%20no%20difference%20between%20going%20online%20for%20news%20versus%20for%20social%20interaction.%20Gen%20Zers%20approach%20most%20of%20their%20digital%20experience%20in%20what%20the%20researchers%20call%20%26quot%3Btimepass%26quot%3B%20mode%2C%20just%20looking%20to%20not%20be%20bored.%20If%20they%20want%20to%20answer%20a%20question%20or%20learn%20something%20new%2C%20they%20might%20turn%20to%20a%20search%20engine%2C%20but%20they're%20acquiring%20new%20information%20mainly%20via%20their%20social%20feeds%2C%20which%20are%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ealgorithmically%20pruned%20to%20reflect%20what%20they%20care%20about%20and%20who%20they%20trust.%20In%20short%2C%20they've%20created%20their%20own%20filters%20to%20process%20an%20onslaught%20of%20digitized%20information.%20Only%20the%20important%20stuff%20shows%20up%2C%20and%20if%20something%20shows%20up%2C%20it%20must%20be%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224260%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20quadrant%20chart%20with%20colored%20ballooning%20regions%20showing%20the%20ways%20Gen%20Zers%20spend%20time%20online%2C%20graphed%20on%20axes%20from%20%26quot%3Blight%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bheavy%26quot%3B%20content%20and%20its%20social%20obligation%20level%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6671da06a76074d191cd08e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222168%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGen%20Zers%20told%20researchers%20they%20spend%20most%20of%20their%20digital%20lives%20in%20%26quot%3Btimepass%26quot%3B%20mode%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0engaging%20in%20light%2C%20obligation-free%20content.%3Cp%3EJigsaw%20and%20Gemic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20don't%20read%20long%20articles.%20And%20they%20don't%20trust%20anything%20with%20ads%2C%20or%20paywalls%2C%20or%20pop-ups%20asking%20for%20donations%20or%20subscriptions.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20making%20clickbait%2C%20you%20have%20zero%20faith%20in%20your%20content%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20subject%20told%20the%20researchers.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20news%20sources%20%E2%80%94%20even%20CNN%20and%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%E2%80%94%20do%20clickbait.%20I%20throw%20those%20articles%20away%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gen%20Z%2C%20the%20online%20world%20resembles%20the%20stratified%2C%20cliquish%20lunchroom%20of%20a%201980s%20teen%20movie.%20Instead%20of%20listening%20to%20stuffy%20old%20teachers%2C%20like%20CNN%20and%20the%20Times%2C%20they%20take%20their%20cues%20from%20online%20influencers%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20queen%20bees%20and%20quarterback%20bros%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20social%20hierarchy.%20The%20influencers'%20personal%20experience%20makes%20them%20authentic%2C%20and%20they%20speak%20Gen%20Z's%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGen%20Zers%20will%20have%20a%20favorite%20influencer%20or%20set%20of%20influencers%20who%20they%20essentially%20outsource%20their%20trust%20to%2C%20and%20then%20they're%20incredibly%20loyal%20to%20everything%20that%20influencer%20is%20saying%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Beth%20Goldberg%2C%20Jigsaw's%20head%20of%20research.%20%26quot%3BIt%20becomes%20extremely%20costly%20to%20fall%20out%20of%20that%20influencer's%20group%2C%20because%20they're%20getting%20all%20their%20information%20from%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20means%20that%20Gen%20Z%20is%20any%20less%20intelligent%20or%20diligent%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethan%20other%20generations.%20They%20know%20how%20to%20research%20something%20more%20deeply.%20It's%20just%20that%2C%20usually%2C%20they%20don't%20wanna.%20%26quot%3BThey%20tap%20into%20those%20critical%20literacy%20skills%20in%20a%20really%20small%20proportion%20of%20the%20time%20they%20spend%20online%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldberg%20says.%20If%20they're%20prepping%20for%20an%20argument%20they%20know%20they're%20going%20to%20have%2C%20or%20when%20they%20have%20to%20make%20big%20life%20decisions%20about%20schools%20or%20investments%2C%20they're%20willing%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20drudgery%20of%20factfinding.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20time%2C%20they're%20spending%20their%20time%20mindlessly%20in%20timepass%20mode.%20Veracity%20was%20not%20only%20not%20top%20of%20mind%2C%20it%20actually%20wasn't%20important%20to%20them%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20one%20subject%20shared%20a%20fake%20image%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20running%20from%20the%20NYPD%2C%20the%20researchers%20challenged%20them%20on%20it.%20%26quot%3BThey%20kind%20of%20shrugged%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldberg%20says.%20From%20the%20subject's%20perspective%2C%20they%20were%20using%20their%20critical%20thinking%20and%20media-literacy%20skills.%20After%20all%2C%20Trump%20was%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20headed%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hush-money-trial-verdict-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20criminal%20trial%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20%3Cem%3Ecould%20have%3C%2Fem%3E%20been%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20things%20like%20diet%20or%20wellness%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20will%20just%20try%20it%20on%20their%20own%20bodies%20and%20see%20if%20it%20works.%20They%20perceive%20that%20as%20a%20safe%20way%20to%20do%20their%20own%20research%2C%20mostly%20because%20it's%20not%20hurting%20anyone%20else.%20If%20that%20new%20diet%20or%20exercise%20regimen%20%26quot%3Bworks%26quot%3B%20on%20their%20body%2C%20that's%20more%20believable%20than%20data%20showing%20its%20effects%20on%20a%20whole%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20facty-sounding%20stuff%20does%20manage%20to%20sneak%20into%20Gen%20Z's%20feeds%20%E2%80%94%20claims%20about%20what%20constitutes%20a%20healthy%20diet%2C%20or%20what%20Trump%20would%20do%20as%20president%2C%20or%20whether%20Ukraine%20or%20Russia%20is%20to%20blame%20for%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20likely%20to%20head%20straight%20for%20the%20comments%3Cstrong%3E.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThat's%20partly%20because%20they%20know%20the%20digital%20hoi%20polloi%20will%20quickly%20unmask%20any%20fake%20news.%20But%20it's%20also%20because%20they're%20concerned%20about%20whether%20the%20news%20%E2%80%94%20or%20a%20particular%20reaction%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20might%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20cancelable%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221835%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20chart%2C%20in%20blue%20gradients%2C%20showing%20a%20linear%20journey%20of%20online%20search%20getting%20more%20informed%20and%20Gen%20Z's%20more%20chaotic%20approach%20bouncing%20among%20the%20algo%2C%20comments%2C%20and%20experience.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66708d1e764df161125a8405%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22839%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERather%20than%20engaging%20in%20a%20more%20traditional%2C%20information-seeking%20journey%20that%20seeks%20to%20answer%20a%20specific%20question%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20figure%20stuff%20out%20by%20bouncing%20around%20online.%3Cp%3EJigsaw%20and%20Gemic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCancel%20culture%20came%20to%20be%20a%20thing%20as%20they%20were%20growing%20up.%20They%20were%20trained%20and%20attend%20to%20how%20to%20perform%2C%20and%20not%20perform%2C%20to%20avoid%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Goldberg.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20getting%20trusted%20information%20from%20closed%20group%20chats%20or%20followers%20with%20private%20feeds%2C%20so%20they're%20able%20to%20perform%20that%20they're%20part%20of%20an%20in-group%20and%20can%20perform%20specific%20social%20signals.%26quot%3B%20For%20Gen%20Z%2C%20checking%20what%20other%20people%20are%20saying%20in%20the%20comments%20isn't%20shallow.%20It's%20a%20matter%20of%20social%20life%20or%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20sounds%20like%20a%20generation%20that%20will%20believe%20any%20flimflam%20they%20encounter%20and%20never%20subscribe%20to%20a%20newspaper%2C%20well%2C%20the%20researchers%20at%20Jigsaw%20worry%20about%20that%20too.%20But%20the%20good%20news%20is%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20aren't%20seeing%20as%20much%20intentional%20falsehood%20as%20you%20might%20think.%20Research%20shows%20that%20most%20mis-%20and%20disinformation%20is%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41586-024-07417-w%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emade%20and%20consumed%20by%20a%20dwindling%20minority%20of%20users%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20seek%20it%20out%2C%20not%20sprayed%20algorithmically%20into%20the%20eyeballs%20of%20credulous%2C%20internet-surfing%20teens.%20%26quot%3BCasual%20consumption%20of%20silly%20TikToks%20is%20very%20unlikely%20to%20lead%20someone%20into%20a%20dark%20corner%20of%20hate%20or%20misinformation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20David%20Rothschild%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Microsoft%20Research%20who%20studies%20online%20behavior.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20highly%20likely%20that%20if%20they%20get%20there%2C%20they%20%3Cem%3Echose%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20get%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20us%20are%20consuming%20less%20formal%20news%20content%20these%20days%2C%20like%20TV%20or%20newspapers.%20And%20like%20Gen%20Z%2C%20we're%20all%20relying%20more%20and%20more%20on%20our%20social%20networks%20to%20tell%20us%20what's%20going%20on.%20A%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fjournalism%2F2024%2F06%2F12%2Fhow-americans-get-news-on-tiktok-x-facebook-and-instagram%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudy%20from%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20most%20users%20on%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20X%2C%20and%20TikTok%20encounter%20news%20frequently.%20On%20X%2C%20it%20most%20often%20comes%20from%20the%20media%20outlets%20and%20journalists%20who%20actually%20produced%20the%20news.%20On%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%2C%20it%20comes%20via%20family%20and%20friends%20whose%20viewpoints%2C%20for%20better%20or%20worse%2C%20you%20already%20know.%20But%20on%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20with%20its%20disproportionately%20younger%20user%20base%20%E2%80%94%20the%20source%20is%20usually%20influencers.%20They%20aggregate%2C%20meta-analyze%2C%20and%20pre-digest%20what%20other%20sources%20are%20saying.%20Maybe%20that's%20why%20users%20on%20TikTok%2C%20compared%20with%20other%20platforms%2C%20say%20they're%20unlikely%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bworn%20out%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20news%20they%20see.%20Someone%20else%20already%20did%20the%20hard%20work%3B%20they're%20getting%20the%20executive%20summary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20clickbait-avoidant%20Gen%20Zers%20might%20suspect%2C%20Jigsaw's%20interest%20in%20their%20online%20behavior%20isn't%20purely%20academic.%20The%20Google%20subsidiary%20makes%20software%20called%20Perspective%20that%20lots%20of%20news%20outlets%20%E2%80%94%20including%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%E2%80%94%20use%20to%20moderate%20their%20comment%20sections.%20The%20new%20iteration%20of%20Perspective%20incorporates%20Jigsaw's%20latest%20findings%2C%20elevating%20comments%20that%20contain%20warm%20and%20fuzzy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fknightcolumbia.org%2Fcontent%2Fbridging-systems%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3Bbridging%26quot%3B%20sentiments%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20curiosity%20and%20reasonableness%2C%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20section.%20The%20aim%20is%20to%20reach%20Gen%20Z%20readers%20where%20they%20live%20%E2%80%94%20scrolling%20through%20the%20comments%20%E2%80%94%20and%20turn%20them%20into%20subscribers.%20By%20studying%20Gen%20Z%20in%20the%20wild%2C%20Jigsaw%20can%20lay%20better%20traps%20for%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2404.05429%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20their%20native%20habitat%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20Gen%20Xer%2C%20I'm%20inherently%20skeptical%20of%20broad%20pronouncements%20about%20the%20up-and-coming%20generation.%20You%20should%20have%20heard%20some%20of%20the%20stuff%20boomers%20said%20about%20us.%20(Not%20that%20we%20cared.%20Like%2C%20whatever.)%20But%20I'll%20confess%20that%20I%20worried%20about%20the%20idea%20that%20Gen%20Z%20checks%20the%20comments%20to%20decide%20what%20to%20believe.%20So%2C%20after%20a%20therapeutic%20clutch%20at%20my%20pearls%2C%20I%20figured%20I'd%20better%20check%20it%20out.%20To%20evaluate%20Jigsaw's%20research%2C%20I%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eperformed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20scientific%20gut%20check%3A%20I%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elooked%20at%20Google%20Scholar%20to%20see%20how%20many%20other%20researchers%20had%20cited%20the%20study.%20That's%20a%20standard%20metric%20for%20how%20much%20a%20field%20values%20any%20given%20journal%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20I%20realized%3A%20I%20was%20basically%20checking%20the%20comments.%20We%20all%20do%20it%20%E2%80%94%20we%20look%20for%20lots%20of%20links%2C%20for%205-star%20reviews%2C%20for%20what%20the%20replies%20say.%20These%20are%20all%20valid%20ways%20to%20surf%20the%20modern%20social-informational%20ecosystem.%20The%20kids%20are%20all%20right%2C%20and%20all%20%3Cem%3Eright%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20wondered%20what%20Gen%20Zers%20themselves%20might%20make%20of%20Jigsaw's%20research.%20Conveniently%2C%20two%20of%20them%20live%20in%20my%20house%20and%20call%20me%20Dad.%20So%20I%20texted%20them%20the%20findings%2C%20along%20with%20a%20question-mark%20emoji.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20seems%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20younger%20one%20replied.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you%20know%20not%20%3Cem%3Eall%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20us%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20counted%20myself%20lucky%20%E2%80%94%20that%20was%20more%20of%20a%20response%20than%20Goldberg%20got.%20%26quot%3BWe%20always%20share%20the%20final%20results%20with%20respondents%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20But%20when%20Goldberg%20asked%20her%20subjects%20what%20they%20thought%20of%20her%20research%2C%20true%20to%20her%20findings%2C%20all%20she%20heard%20back%20was%20the%20gravid%20silence%20of%20teenagers%20looking%20at%20their%20phones.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20sure%20how%20many%20of%20our%20Gen%20Zers%20read%20our%20papers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20concluded%20ruefully.%20No%20comment%20section%2C%20no%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-trusted-news-source-online-comme