F66670150e079049018175456%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flauren-sanchez-most-daring-outfits-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lauren%20S%C3%A1nchez%20has%20always%20had%20a%20daring%20fashion%20sense%2C%20but%20her%20outfits%20have%20become%20especially%20bold%20during%20her%20relationship%20with%20Jeff%20Bezos.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22akrause%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Krause)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flauren-sanchez-most-daring-outfits-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Revisiting%20The%20Emergency%3A%20The%20Prelude%2C%20The%20Clampdown%20And%20The%20Resistance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%2021-month%20Emergency%20imposed%20by%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20was%20not%20just%20a%20dark%20period%20for%20Indian%20democracy%20that%20demonstrated%20how%20absolute%20power%20corrupts%20absolutely%2C%20but%20a%20landmark%20event%20that%20altered%20the%20course%20of%20Indian%20politics%20and%20displayed%20how%20the%20Indian%20voter%20can%20forgive%20its%20leaders%20for%20many%20excesses%2C%20but%20not%20arrogance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifty%20years%20on%2C%20most%20of%20the%20key%20players%20that%20starred%20in%20that%20tumultuous%20time%20are%20no%20more%2C%20but%20the%20Emergency's%20example%20is%20cited%20every%20time%20brute%20power%20threatens%20to%20undermine%20the%20citizen's%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20look%20at%20that%20watershed%20event%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22This%20iconic%20photo%20by%20Raghu%20Rai%20captures%20Indira%20Gandhis%20authority%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22This%20iconic%20photo%20by%20Raghu%20Rai%20captures%20Indira%20Gandhis%20authority%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F7lhctjp_indira-gandhi_625x300_25_June_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20iconic%20photo%20by%20Raghu%20Rai%20captures%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20authority%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Background%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20the%20Emergency%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20look%20at%20how%20tall%20the%20stature%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20in%20the%20years%20preceding%20it.%20The%20Congress%20split%20in%201969%20and%20this%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20concentration%20of%20power%20in%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20office.%20In%20the%201971%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20the%20Congress%20won%20352%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20on%20Mrs%20Gandhi's%20slogan%20of%20Garibi%20Hatao%20and%20she%20established%20herself%20as%20the%20'real%20Congress'%2C%20edging%20out%20the%20party's%20old%20guard%20that%20was%20known%20as%20Congress%20(O).%20India's%20victory%20against%20Pakistan%20in%20the%201971%20Bangladesh%20War%20of%20Independence%20brought%20her%20into%20international%20limelight%20and%20earned%20her%20praise%20from%20even%20the%20Opposition.%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%20then%20a%20Jana%20Sangh%20leader%2C%20likened%20Mrs%20Gandhi%20to%20Goddess%20Durga%20and%20she%20was%20at%20her%20zenith%20of%20popularity.%20Shortly%20after%20the%201971%20war%2C%20she%20was%20awarded%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%2C%20ironically%20during%20her%20tenure%20as%20Prime%20Minister.%20The%20Economist%20went%20so%20far%20as%20to%20call%20her%20the%20Empress%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Landmark%20Judgment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20events%20in%20history%20start%20with%20a%20ripple.%20Raj%20Narain%2C%20then%20a%20leader%20of%20Samyukt%20Socialist%20Party%2C%20had%20lost%20against%20Mrs%20Gandhi%20in%20the%201971%20polls%20by%20a%20margin%20of%201.11%20lakh%20votes%20in%20Rae%20Bareli.%20Following%20his%20defeat%2C%20Mr%20Narain%20accused%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20misusing%20state%20machinery%20for%20poll%20purposes.%20Mrs%20Gandhi%20was%20accused%20of%20using%20in%20her%20election%20campaign%20the%20services%20of%20a%20government%20official%20and%20a%20rostrum.%20On%20June%2012%2C%201975%2C%20Justice%20Jagmohanlal%20Sinha%20of%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20found%20the%20prime%20minister%20guilty%20and%20declared%20her%20election%20null%20and%20void.%20She%20was%20also%20banned%20from%20contesting%20any%20election%20for%20six%20years.%20The%20Times%20of%20India%20compared%20the%20verdict%20to%20%26quot%3Bfiring%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20for%20a%20traffic%20ticket%26quot%3B.%20Mrs%20Gandhi%20challenged%20the%20order%20in%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20said%20that%20while%20she%20could%20continue%20as%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20she%20won't%20have%20voting%20rights%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20till%20her%20plea%20was%20decided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Law%20Tweaks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Emergency%20was%20announced%2C%20the%20government%20prepared%20the%20stage.%20Draconian%20laws%20that%20would%20later%20be%20used%20to%20target%20political%20opponents%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Maintenance%20of%20Internal%20Security%20Act%20(MISA)%2C%20were%20passed%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20Congress's%20brute%20majority.%20The%20Defence%20of%20India%20Act%2C%20a%20set%20of%20laws%20enacted%20during%20the%201962%20war%20with%20China%2C%20was%20renewed%20right%20after%20Emergency%20was%20imposed.%20This%20law%20suspended%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20anyone%20arrested%20under%20two.%20Among%20its%20draconian%20aspects%20was%20a%20provision%20for%20detaining%20a%20person%20without%20explanation.%20The%20Conservation%20of%20Foreign%20Exchange%20and%20Prevention%20of%20Smuggling%20Activities%20Act%20was%20another%20law%20used%20to%20target%20political%20rivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.nd