ow%2F111253096.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Greater%20Expectations%3A%20Why%20China%20Is%20Going%20Nuclear%20'Faster%20Than%20Ever'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fjfceq2jo_xi-jinping-reuters-_625x300_07_December_23.jpeg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecent%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnuclear-warheads-being-kept-operational-worldwide-watchdog-5905625%5C%22%3EStockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute%20(SIPRI)%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-has-more-nuclear-weapons-than-pakistan-report-5909387%5C%22%3Ethe%20world's%20nuclear%20powers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20continuing%20to%20expand%20investment%20in%20strengthening%20their%20arsenals.%20While%20the%20total%20number%20of%20warheads%20around%20the%20world%20is%20declining%2C%20the%20number%20of%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20is%20increasing.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-putin-friends-are-helping-russia-upend-the-us-led-world-order-5691040%5C%22%3EUS%20and%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20of%20course%2C%20account%20for%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20nuclear%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20China%20that%20is%20reportedly%20expanding%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal%20%26quot%3Bfaster%20than%20any%20other%20country%26quot%3B.%20SIPRI's%20researchers%20estimated%20the%20Chinese%20arsenal%20to%20be%20around%20500%20warheads%2C%20as%20of%20January%202024.%20As%20per%20the%20US%20Defense%20Department's%20estimate%2C%20China%20will%20likely%20have%20over%201%2C000%20operational%20warheads%20by%202030.%20More%20importantly%2C%20the%20SIPRI%20report%20argues%20that%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20China%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20some%20warheads%20on%20high%20operational%20alert.%20In%20addition%2C%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20there%20have%20been%20increasing%20reports%20on%20Chinese%20efforts%20to%20expand%20the%20number%20of%20its%20land-%2C%20sea-%2C%20and%20air-based%20delivery%20platforms%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20such%20as%20Intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20(ICBM)%20silos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BAssured%20Retaliation%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20nuclear%20strategy%20centres%20around%20deterrence%20through%20%26quot%3Bassured%20retaliation%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20survive%20an%20initial%20attack%20and%20retaliate%20with%20nuclear%20strikes%20that%20inflict%20unacceptable%20damage%20on%20the%20aggressor.%20Moreover%2C%20like%20India%2C%20China%20has%20a%20long-standing%20no-first-use%20policy.%20Despite%20this%2C%20as%20detailed%20above%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20steady%20effort%20by%20Beijing%20to%20expand%20and%20modernise%20its%20nuclear%20forces.%20Three%20factors%20are%20important%20to%20grasp%20to%20understand%20why%20this%20has%20been%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fin-1-year-chinas-nuclear-arsenal-up-by-11-times-that-of-indias-5915463%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0Explained%3A%20India%20Has%20More%20Nukes%20Than%20Pak%2C%20But%20China%20Races%20Ahead%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20Chinese%20assessments%20of%20the%20international%20security%20landscape%2C%20particularly%20US%20policy%2C%20have%20undergone%20tremendous%20changes%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%20China's%202019%20defence%20white%20paper%20was%20critical%20of%20adjustments%20in%20the%20American%20national%20security%20and%20defence%20strategies%2C%20while%20also%20warning%20of%20arms%20races.%20The%20Sino-US%20relationship%20has%20only%20worsened%20since.%20Increasingly%2C%20Beijing%20has%20come%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20US%20is%20pursuing%20a%20strategy%20of%20containment.%20Part%20of%20this%20approach%20entails%20strengthening%20American%20conventional%20military%20superiority%20while%20modernising%20strategic%20forces.%20Of%20particular%20concern%20has%20been%20the%20American%20discourse%20around%20'low-yield'%20or%20tactical%20nuclear%20weapons.%20Chinese%20analysts%20have%20argued%20that%20US%20policy%20appears%20to%20be%20lowering%20the%20threshold%20for%20the%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20concern%20in%20Beijing%20appears%20to%20be%20that%20American%20missile%20defence%20capabilities%20and%20new%20conventional%20systems%2C%20along%20with%20improvements%20in%20cyber%20and%20electronic%20warfare%2C%20could%20undermine%20China's%20retaliatory%20strike%20capability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BMaintain%20Readiness%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202019%20defence%20white%20paper%2C%20therefore%2C%20called%20on%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20to%20%26quot%3Bmaintain%20the%20appropriate%20level%20of%20readiness%20and%20enhance%20strategic%20deterrence%20capability%26quot%3B.%20Subsequently%2C%20in%20March%202021%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%20directed%20the%20military%20to%20%26quot%3Baccelerate%20the%20construction%20of%20advanced%20strategic%20deterrent%26quot%3B%20capabilities.%20Finally%2C%20in%20his%20work%20report%20to%20the%2020th%20Party%20Congress%2C%20Xi%20committed%20to%20establishing%20%26quot%3Ba%20strong%20system%20of%20strategic%20deterrence%26quot%3B%20and%20increasing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20proportion%20of%20new-domain%20forces%20with%20new%20combat%20capabilities%26quot%3B.%20This%20is%20particularly%20critical%20given%20the%20heightened%20tensions%20around%20Taiwan.%20A%20modernised%20Chinese%20nuclear%20force%20potentially%20provides%20greater%20room%20for%20manoeuvre%20for%20Beijing%20in%20case%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchina-could-take-control-of-taiwan-without-firing-a-shot-warns-report-5949602%5C%22%3Econflict%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchina-increases-defence-budget-by-7-2-amid-rising-regional-tensions-5179889%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0China%20Increases%20Defence%20Budget%20By%207.2%25%20Amid%20Rising%20Regional%20Tensions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20as%20per%20the%202019%20defence%20white%20paper%2C%20one%20of%20the%20goals%20of%20enhancing%20strategic%20deterrence%20capability%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bmaintain%20international%20strategic%20stability%26quot%3B.%20This%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20a%20significant%20expansion%20of%20the%20goals%20of%20Chinese%20defence%20policy%20from%20simply%20safeguarding%20national%20sovereignty%20and%20security.%20It%20also%20is%20indicative%20of%20what%20Beijing%20views%20as%20necessary%20instruments%20of%20power%20that%20great%20powers%20must%20possess.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20there%20is%20an%20element%20of%20status-seeking%20that%20is%20driving%20the%20Chinese%20nuclear%20modernisation%20programme.%20For%20instance%2C%20early%20in%20his%20reign%20in%20December%202012%2C%20Xi%20had%20termed%20the%20Second%20Artillery%20Corps%2C%20which%20was%20later%20upgraded%20to%20the%20PLA%20Rocket%20Force%2C%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20strategic%20pillar%20of%20China's%20great%20power%20status%26quot%3B.%20This%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20Beijing%20desires%20nuclear%20parity%20with%20the%20US%20or%20Russia.%20Rather%2C%20it%20implies%20that%20nuclear%20power%20is%20being%20viewed%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20power%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20cultivated%20to%20achieve%20political%20equality%20among%20major%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Stalled%20US-China%20Talks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20dovetails%20into%20the%20third%20and%20final%20point%2C%20i.e.%2C%20building%20negotiation%20power%20and%20setting%20global%20rules.%20After%20an%20extremely%20long%20hiatus%2C%20China%20and%20the%20US%20resumed%20official%20nuclear%20dialogue%20in%20November%20last%20year.%20Both%20sides%20described%20the%20dialogue%20as%20%26quot%3Bcandid%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bin-depth%26quot%3B%2C%20but%20there%20were%20no%20significant%20outcomes.%20The%20US%20side%20demanded%20greater%20%26quot%3Btransparency%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsubstantive%20engagement%26quot%3B%20from%20China%2C%20while%20Beijing%20stressed%20the%20importance%20of%20%26quot%3Bmutual%20respect%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20need%20to%20adhere%20to%20%26quot%3Bthe%20vision%20of%20common%2C%20comprehensive%2C%20cooperative%20and%20sustainable%20security%26quot%3B.%20More%20substantive%20talks%20have%20since%20not%20progressed%2C%20although%20the%20first%20Track%20II%20dialogue%20between%20the%20two%20sides%20in%20five%20years%20was%20held%20in%20March.%20China%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20moved%20to%20call%20on%20nuclear-armed%20states%20to%20negotiate%20a%20no-first-use%20treaty%20or%20political%20declaration.%20Beijing%20understands%20that%20shaping%20new%20rules%20can%20only%20be%20done%20from%20a%20position%20of%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20an%20Indian%20perspective%2C%20therefore%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20not%20view%20China's%20nuclear%20force%20modernisation%20simply%20from%20the%20prism%20of%20parity%20and%20asymmetry.%20There%20are%20broader%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20great%20power%20conflagrations%20leading%20to%20a%20nuclear%20exchange%2C%20which%20must%20be%20taken%20into%20account.%20Some%20of%20these%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20the%20threat%20of%20increased%20proliferation%20and%20support%20for%20Pakistan%2C%20are%20a%20matter%20of%20deeper%20concern.%20Others%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20such%20as%20the%20call%20for%20a%20no-first-use%20treaty%2C%20can%20provide%20opportunities%20for%20making%20common%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Manoj%20Kewalramani%20is%20the%20Chairperson%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20Studies%20Programme%20at%20the%20Takshashila%20Institution.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719301800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fjfceq2jo_xi-jinping-reuters-_625x300_07_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fgreater-expectations-why-china-is-going-nuclear-faster-than-ever-5965117%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20per%20the%20US%20Defense%20Department's%20estimate%2C%20China%20will%20likely%20have%20over%201%2C000%20operational%20warheads%20by%202030.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fgreater-expectations-why-china-is-going-nuclear-faster-than-ever-5965117%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fgreater-expectations-why-china-is-going-nuclear-faster-than-ever-5965117%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fgreater-expectations-why-china-is-going-nuclear-faster-than-ever-5965117%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Kalki%202898%20AD'%20to%20have%20200%20cr%20opening%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719301700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111252854%2Cimgsize-40558.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Fkalki-2898-ad-advance-box-office-the-amitabh-bachchan-prabhas-deepika-padukone-starrer-expected-to-have-rs-200-crore-opening-worldwide%2Farticleshow%2F111252904.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F111252904.cms