Ffilm%2Fasia%2Fprosenjit-chatterjee-devi-chowdhurani-india-uk-co-production-1236046595%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Need%20Chinese%20Students%20In%20Humanities%2C%20Indian%20For%20Sciences%3A%20US%20Diplomat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20should%20welcome%20more%20students%20from%20China%2C%20but%20to%20study%20the%20humanities%20rather%20than%20sciences%2C%20the%20second-ranked%20US%20diplomat%20said%20on%20Monday%2C%20noting%20that%20US%20universities%20are%20limiting%20Chinese%20students'%20access%20to%20sensitive%20technology%20given%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Kurt%20Campbell%20said%20not%20enough%20Americans%20were%20studying%20science%2C%20technology%2C%20engineering%20and%20mathematics.%20He%20said%20the%20US%20needed%20to%20recruit%20more%20international%20students%20for%20those%20fields%2C%20but%20from%20India%20-%20an%20increasingly%20important%20US%20security%20partner%20-%20not%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Chinese%20students%20have%20made%20up%20the%20largest%20foreign%20student%20body%20in%20the%20US%20and%20totaled%20nearly%20290%2C000%20in%20the%202022%2F23%20academic%20year.%20But%20some%20in%20academia%20and%20civil%20society%20argue%20that%20deteriorating%20US-China%20relations%20and%20concerns%20about%20theft%20of%20US%20expertise%2C%20have%20derailed%20scientific%20cooperation%20and%20subjected%20Chinese%20students%20to%20unwarranted%20suspicion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20like%20to%20see%20more%20Chinese%20students%20coming%20to%20the%20United%20States%20to%20study%20humanities%20and%20social%20sciences%2C%20not%20particle%20physics%2C%26quot%3B%20Campbell%20told%20the%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%20think-tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECampbell%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20China%20Initiative%20introduced%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20intended%20to%20combat%20Chinese%20espionage%20and%20intellectual%20property%20theft%2C%20which%20ended%20under%20the%20Biden%20administration%20after%20critics%20said%20it%20spurred%20racial%20profiling%20of%20Asian%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECampbell%20said%20US%20universities%20had%20made%20%26quot%3Bcareful%20attempts%26quot%3B%20to%20support%20continuing%20higher%20education%20for%20Chinese%20students%2C%20but%20had%20also%20been%20%26quot%3Bcareful%20about%20the%20labs%2C%20some%20of%20the%20activities%20of%20Chinese%20students.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20curtail%20and%20to%20limit%20certain%20kinds%20of%20access%2C%20and%20we%20have%20seen%20that%20generally%2C%20particularly%20in%20technological%20programs%20across%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECampbell%20said%20some%20had%20suggested%20that%20China%20was%20the%20only%20source%20to%20make%20up%20the%20shortage%20of%20science%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20that%20the%20largest%20increase%20that%20we%20need%20to%20see%20going%20forward%20would%20be%20much%20larger%20numbers%20of%20Indian%20students%20that%20come%20to%20study%20in%20American%20universities%20on%20a%20range%20of%20technology%20and%20other%20fields.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECampbell%20said%20the%20US%20had%20to%20be%20careful%20to%20not%20eliminate%20links%20between%20China%20and%20the%20US%2C%20but%20officials%20in%20Beijing%20were%20largely%20to%20blame%20for%20any%20withering%20in%20academic%2C%20business%20or%20non-profit%20sector%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20has%20been%20China%20that%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20kinds%20of%20activities%20that%20we%20would%20like%20to%20see%20sustaining%2C%26quot%3B%20Campbell%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20foreign%20executives%20and%20philanthropists%20were%20wary%20about%20long-term%20stays%20in%20China%20due%20to%20concerns%20about%20personal%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719298800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndt